From 4049570254d12009faaafb751494e35f6e7339bd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 18:31:47 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(dream): promote = fix-and-merge under the standing
 umbrella #2663

The dream PROMOTE verb used to file a fresh needs-triage issue per grounded
gap. Those piled up because IssueImplementerScanner skips needs-triage. Drive
each grounded gap to a MERGED fix tracked under one standing umbrella issue
(souliane/teatree#2663, reused daily, never closed) instead.

- New teatree.loops.dream.umbrella_ledger: upsert a deduped checkbox under the
  umbrella keyed on a stable gap key (invisible <!-- dream-gap <key> --> marker),
  schedule the fix via Ticket.schedule_coding() + the existing orchestrator path,
  and reconcile on merge (check the box + retire the linked ConsolidatedMemory
  off the fix Ticket's authoritative MERGED state).
- Remove the create_issue(needs-triage) calls in promote_memory
  (_file_one_gap/file_core_gap_tickets) and compliance (escalate_recurrences);
  the binding-reconciliation filer still files a deduped issue for a human.
- New CodeHostBackend.update_issue(issue_url, body) extension method edits the
  umbrella body in place (GitHub PATCH .../issues/<n>, GitLab PUT .../issues/<iid>).
- No new model / no migration: an in-flight gap is an existing Ticket row
  (gap/memory/umbrella linkage in extra) + its ConsolidatedMemory entry.
- Fold in two stale :func: doc-refs in llm_eval_proposer (engine -> sdk_distiller).

Also finish the in-flight github backend transport extraction: move the gh CLI
request helpers (_run_gh / _gh_api_* / _parse_issue_ref) into a new
teatree.backends.github.api module, mirroring teatree.backends.gitlab.api, so
github/client.py keeps only the cross-host Protocol surface. Retarget the helper
patch targets in test_github_backend.py to the new module.
